%20law%20are%20punishable%20by%20fines%20of%20up%20to%20%2410%2C000%20or%20imprisonment%20of%20up%20to%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Musk%20ran%20afoul%20of%20the%20law%2C%20it%20would%20fall%20to%20the%20Justice%20Department%20to%20enforce%20it.%20Richard%20Briffault%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Columbia%20Law%20School%2C%20said%20it%20would%20be%20surprising%20to%20see%20such%20an%20action%20so%20close%20to%20Election%20Day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20as%20it%20is%20a%20pretty%20aggressive%20move%20on%20his%20part%20to%20do%20this%2C%20it%20would%20also%20be%20an%20aggressive%20move%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20to%20do%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Briffault%2C%20who%20studies%20campaign%20finance%20law%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBriffault%20said%20Musk's%20gambit%20may%20violate%20%26quot%3Bthe%20spirit%20of%20the%20law%2C%20but%20not%20the%20letter%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20law.%20%26quot%3BIf%20this%20was%20just%20set%20up%20as%20'I'll%20pay%20you%20to%20register%20to%20vote%2C'%20that%20would%20be%20illegal%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20ambiguity%2C%20Briffault%20said%2C%20because%20most%20of%20the%20participants%20have%20likely%20been%20on%20the%20voting%20rolls%20long%20before%20Musk%20even%20conceived%20of%20the%20giveaway.%20Briffault%20added%20that%20though%20Musk's%20%26quot%3Bclear%20intent%20was%20to%20incentivize%26quot%3B%20pro-Trump%20voters%20to%20register%20to%20vote%2C%20he%20%26quot%3Bmight%20be%20able%20to%20get%20away%20with%26quot%3B%20saying%20he's%20not%20trying%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20election%20law%20experts%20also%20said%20that%20Musk%20is%20either%20barely%20toeing%20the%20line%20or%20has%20outright%20broken%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20illegal%20to%20give%20out%20money%20on%20the%20condition%20that%20recipients%20register%20as%20voters%2C%26quot%3B%20Adav%20Noti%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Campaign%20Legal%20Center%2C%20said