%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e0e19d4e94e8670703ad7a2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221045%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20is%20not%20pictured.%3Cp%3Eskynesher%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMy%20stepfather's%20dementia%20caused%20him%20to%20forget%20to%20make%20mortgage%20payments%2C%20which%20led%20to%20eviction%20for%20him%20and%20my%20mom.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHe%20had%20a%20%241.5%20million%20life%20insurance%20policy%2C%20which%20my%20mom%20used%20as%20leverage%20to%20get%20a%20loan%20for%20his%20care.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMy%20mom's%20experience%20convinced%20me%20to%20buy%20a%2020-year%2C%20%24500%2C000%20term%20life%20policy%20of%20my%20own%2C%20at%20%2428%20a%20month.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELife%20insurance%20was%20never%20one%20of%20my%20financial%20priorities.%20In%20fact%2C%20if%20you%20asked%20me%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20would%20have%20told%20you%20that%20buying%20a%20policy%20was%20for%20suckers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20in%20my%2030s.%20Married%2C%20but%20no%20kids.%20Until%20recently%2C%20I%20figured%20I%20had%20plenty%20of%20time%20to%20sock%20away%20some%20funds%20to%20cushion%20the%20blow%20if%20anything%20should%20happen%20to%20me.%20Why%20would%20I%20need%20life%20insurance%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20I%20put%20my%20focus%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20young%20men%20do%3A%20maximizing%20my%20earnings%2C%20saving%20what%20I%20could%2C%20and%20filling%20up%20my%20retirement%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20would%20have%20gone%20on%20like%20that%20indefinitely%20%E2%80%94%20until%20the%20day%20my%20mom%20lost%20her%20house.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20life-rattling%20diagnosis%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20October%20evening%2C%20my%20mom%20and%20her%20husband%20%E2%80%94%20my%20stepfather%20%E2%80%94%20went%20out%20for%20dinner%20and%20drinks.%20When%20they%20came%20home%2C%20they%20couldn't%20get%20back%20inside.%20The%20locks%20had%20been%20changed.%20A%20big%20%26quot%3BFORECLOSURE%20NOTICE%26quot%3B%20was%20plastered%20on%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%20was%20confused.%20The%20house%20was%20in%20my%20stepfather's%20name%2C%20and%20he'd%20been%20steadily%20paying%20the%20mortgage.%20Or%20so%20she%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversations%20with%20the%20bank%20would%20reveal%20that%2C%20actually%2C%20my%20stepfather%20hadn't%20made%20a%20single%20payment%20in%20more%20than%20three%20years.%20He'd%20ignored%20phone%20calls%2C%20tossed%20warnings%20away%2C%20and%20never%20told%20my%20mom%20a%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDigging%20deeper%20into%20her%20husband's%20financial%20life%20only%20confused%20her%20more.%20He%20was%20a%20successful%20business%20owner.%20Monthly%20cash%20flows%20would%20have%20more%20than%20covered%20the%20mortgage.%20As%20a%20couple%2C%20they%20had%20plenty%20of%20cash%20in%20the%20bank.%20Enough%20to%20pay%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20mortgage%20off%20completely.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20why%20did%20they%20suddenly%20find%20themselves%20kicked%20out%20of%20their%20home%3F%20Why%20wasn't%20my%20stepfather%20making%20those%20payments%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20an%20accountant%20or%20a%20lawyer%20who%20answered%20these%20questions%20for%20us.%20It%20was%20a%20neurologist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20an%20MRI%2C%20the%20neurologist%20told%20us%20definitively%20that%20my%20stepfather%20wasn't%20being%20malicious.%20He%20didn't%20have%20any%20kind%20of%20scheme%2C%20or%20a%20feud%20with%20the%20bank.%20He%20had%20frontotemporal%20dementia%20(FTD)%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20degenerative%20brain%20disease%20that%20permanently%20rattled%20his%20mind.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20stepfather%20simply%20forgot%20about%20the%20payments.%20Over%20and%20over%20again.%20For%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20my%20mother%2C%20this%20was%20a%20heartbreaking%20diagnosis.%20It%20would%20also%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20a%20very%20expensive%20one.%20Losing%20their%20house%20would%20only%20be%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20fiscal%20complications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spouse%20with%20dementia%20is%20a%20financial%20time%20bomb.%20FTD%20is%20a%20crippling%20disease.%20There%20is%20no%20cure.%20Patients'%20brains%20deteriorate%20at%20an%20unpredictable%20rate%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20telling%20what%20cognitive%20problems%20will%20develop%20along%20the%20way.%20The%20only%20certainty%20for%20my%20mother%20is%20that%2C%20eventually%2C%20my%20stepfather%20will%20need%2024%2F7%20care%20in%20a%20nursing%20home.%20In%20her%20area%2C%20that%20costs%20about%20%248%2C000%20per%20month.%20It's%20possible%20he%20could%20need%20that%20care%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20math%20looks%20grim%2C%20and%20it%20would%20look%20a%20whole%20lot%20worse%20if%20my%20stepfather%20didn't%20have%20a%20%241.5%20million%20term%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flife-insurance%2Fbest-life-insurance-companies%5C%22%3Elife%20insurance%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELife%20insurance%20was%20a%20financial%20lifeline%20for%20my%20mother%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20mortgage%20had%20slipped%20my%20stepfather's%20mind%2C%20the%20life%20insurance%20premiums%20were%20on%20autopay.%20The%20policy%20was%20in%20good%20standing%20when%20my%20stepfather%20got%20his%20diagnosis.%20Obviously%2C%20my%20mother%20couldn't%20claim%20the%20policy%20while%20my%20stepfather%20was%20still%20alive.%20But%20that%20didn't%20mean%20the%20policy%20couldn't%20help%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom's%20financial%20advisor%2C%20Roger%20Deal%2C%20a%20CPA%20with%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sequoiawealthpartners.com%2F%5C%22%3E%20Sequoia%20Wealth%20Partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Omaha%2C%20Nebraska%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20such%20a%20hefty%20policy%20gave%20her%20some%20options.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOption%20one%3A%20She%20could%20sell%20the%20policy%20to%20another%20insurance%20company%20for%20some%20fraction%20of%20its%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20usually%20isn't%20a%20great%20option%20for%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Roger%20explained%20to%20me.%20%26quot%3BThe%20buyer%20company%20is%20going%20to%20look%20over%20your%20case%20with%20a%20fine-tooth%20comb.%20They'll%20have%20their%20own%20medical%20people%2C%20and%20they'll%20come%20to%20a%20new%20decision%20about%20the%20insured%20person's%20insurability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20time%2C%20that%20translates%20to%20a%20lowball%20offer%2C%20even%20for%20very%20generous%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOption%20two%20was%20more%20appealing%20for%20my%20mom%3A%20Use%20the%20policy%20as%20leverage%20to%20secure%20a%20loan%20from%20a%20bank.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBanks%20aren't%20going%20to%20look%20at%20insurability%20at%20all.%20All%20they%20care%20about%20is%20recouping%20their%20loan.%20They'll%20need%20proof%20that%20the%20policy%20is%20real%2C%20and%20that%20the%20insurer%20is%20in%20good%20financial%20standing.%20That's%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Roger%20explained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20stepdad's%20policy%20in%20hand%2C%20Roger%20and%20my%20mom%20went%20to%20a%20local%20bank%20and%20secured%20some%20much-needed%20cash%20to%20help%20defray%20the%20cost%20of%20long-term%20care.%20For%20my%20mom%2C%20this%20got%20her%20some%20vital%20breathing%20room.%20Though%20there's%20no%20telling%20how%20her%20husband's%20disease%20will%20progress%2C%20at%20least%20she%20knows%20she%20has%20the%20assets%20to%20take%20care%20of%20him%20when%20the%20time%20comes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20mother's%20story%20made%20me%20take%20the%20leap%20on%20a%20policy%20for%20myself%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20experience%20with%20my%20stepfather%20was%20a%20wake-up%20call.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20me%2C%20life%20insurance%20had%20always%20been%20a%20little%20morbid.%20Maybe%20I%20wanted%20to%20avoid%20coming%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20George%20Bailey%20did%20in%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20Wonderful%20Life%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20who%20wants%20to%20be%20worth%20more%20dead%20than%20alive%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20my%20mom's%20encounter%20made%20me%20realize%20what%20an%20asset%20life%20insurance%20can%20be.%20Where%20would%20my%20mom%20be%20without%20it%3F%20I%20shudder%20at%20the%20thought.%20And%20if%20I%20had%20dementia%20or%20some%20other%20severe%20disability%2C%20I%20would%20never%20want%20my%20wife%20to%20have%20to%20shoulder%20the%20burden%20of%20my%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20took%20out%20a%2020-year%2C%20%24500%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flife-insurance%2Fbest-term-life-insurance-companies%5C%22%3Eterm%20life%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20annual%20payment%20of%20about%20%24340%20(which%20is%20about%20%2428%20a%20month)%20is%20a%20pittance%20compared%20to%20the%20peace%20of%20mind%20it%20gives%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrontotemporal%20dementia%20is%20exceedingly%20rare.%20But%20all%20the%20same%2C%20it's%20good%20to%20know%20that%20if%20it%20should%20happen%20to%20me%2C%20my%20wife%20will%20have%20options%20to%20deal%20with%20it.%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhen-to-save-money-in-high-yield-savings%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGet%20Life%20Insurance%20Quotes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompare%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flife-insurance%2Fbest-cheap-life-insurance%5C%22%3Eaffordable%20life%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20options%20with%20Policygenius.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20December%202019.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbought-life-insurance-young-after-foreclosure-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729544899000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.inside